text.section:
For purposes of this section, "potentially serious disorder or condition" means:
Hypertension and cardiac conditions;
Acute, severe abdominal pain;
Undiagnosed neurological changes;
Unexplained weight loss or gain in excess of fifteen percent (15%) of the patient's body weight in less than a three (3) month period;
Suspected fracture or dislocation;
Suspected systemic infections;
Serious hemorrhagic disorder;
Acute respiratory distress without a previous history;
Pregnancy;
Diabetes; or
Cancer.
